ted .eslintrc files in Visual Studio Code</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h1>Problems you may face</h1>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>While running eslint fix on the project i got this error</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>AssertionError [ERR_ASSERTION]: Node must be provided when reporting error if location is not provided</p>\n</blockquote>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>to fix it i did a loop on the files in the directory and fix each of them to get the code snippet that cause the previous problem</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">for file in *; do                                            \n    if [ -f &quot;$file&quot; ]; then\n        ../node_modules/eslint/bin/eslint.js &quot;$file&quot; --fix\n    fi\ndone</code></pre></div>","fields":{"slug":"/blog/posts/eslint-configs-react-ts/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"December 28, 2020","title":"Setup eslint configs into your React App (Support TS)","toArabic":null},"timeToRead":2,"wordCount":{"words":91}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/posts/eslint-configs-react-ts/","toArabic":null}}}